            <abstract>
                <p>Neither the author nor the type of this <term key="Qene" ana="#Qene">qǝne</term> are indicated 
                    in the manuscript. 
                    It has been printed in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/FGSB8GYT"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Afawarq1984Yageezqeneyat"/><title level="m">&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;የግእዝ ቅኔያት የስነ ጥበብ ቅርስ። ሁለተኛ ክፍል። ንባቡ ከነትርጓሜው (&lt;/hi&gt;Yagǝʾǝz qǝneyāt yasǝna ṭǝbab qǝrs.  Hulataññā kǝfl.  Nǝbābu kannatǝrgwāmew&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;, Gǝʾǝz &lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;qǝnes&lt;/hi&gt;, the monument of wisdom. Second part. Reading  with interpretationʼ)&lt;/hi&gt;</title><editor><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ʾAfawarq Zawde</t:name></editor><editor><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Qaḍalā Mangǝśtu</t:name></editor><editor><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Malkǝʾa Krǝstos Nabiyu</t:name></editor><editor><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Kǝnafa Rǝgb ʾAttālal</t:name></editor><pubPlace>Addis Ababa</pubPlace><publisher>Bǝrhānǝnnā salām māttamiyā bet</publisher><date>1991</date><citedRange unit="page">66–67</citedRange></bibl>, together 
                    with an Amharic translation, the type being defined as 
                    <term key="Mibazhu" ana="#Mibazhu">mi-bazḫu</term> (composed of three lines). 
                    The manusript witness <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFabb145">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien d'Abbadie 145</ref>
                    shows a slight text variation (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ተሣህሎ፡</foreign> instead of 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተሰቅሎ፡</foreign> as in the printed edition).</p>
