            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" xml:lang="gez">
                    <note>The text is taken from <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFabb145">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien d'Abbadie 145</ref>, fol. 56va
                        (division into verses is indicated with the four dot asterisk ።; 
                        the end of the poem is indicated with the double four dot asterisk ። ።).</note>
                    <ab>                                                  
                        <l n="1">እክለ፡ አበሳሃ፡ ለሄዋን፡ ከመ፡ ተርእየ፡ ኢኮነ፡ በገራህተ፡ ኤዶም፡ ቅድመ።</l> 
                        <l n="2">ዝናመ፡ ተሣህሎ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አምጣነ፡ በመስቀል፡ ቆመ።</l>
                        <l n="3">ዝኒ፡ መስቀል፡ ነገረ፡ ጽድቁ፡ ትሩፍ፡ በአረጋዊ፡ ፈጸመ።</l>                                            
                    </ab>
                               </div>
                <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:id="translationEthio" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7225EklaAbasaha#etiopica">                    
                    <ab>
                        <l n="1">The corn of Ewa’s abuse was not seen in the fields of Edom, as before,</l>
                        <l n="2">Because the rain of mercy, Christ, rose on the Cross.</l>
                        <l n="3">And this Cross completed the matter of His exceeding righteousness through the old man.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
